    "finalTextLength": 1039,
    "finalText": "Go to the project first, then:\n\n1. Open **Commitments** from the project sidebar  \n2. Click **New Commitment**\n3. Choose the type:\n   - **Subcontract** for trade/labor scope\n   - **Purchase Order** for materials, equipment, or services\n4. Fill in the core fields:\n   - **Vendor**\n   - **Title**\n   - **Contract number** if you want to override the auto-number\n   - **Status**\n   - **Scope/description**\n   - **Start date**\n   - **Estimated completion date**\n   - **Default retainage %**\n5. Save it\n6. After that, you can build the **Schedule of Values**, track **commitment change orders**, and invoice against it\n\nWhere it lives:\n- Route: **/[projectId]/commitments**\n- Help article: **Commitments (Subcontracts and Purchase Orders)**\n\nWhat a commitment is in this app:\n- **Subcontract** = contract with a trade partner\n- **PO** = order for materials/equipment/services\n\nOne important point: commitments are tied to a **project vendor/company**, so if the vendor is not already in the project directory, you may need to add them first.\n\nI"
